#: ../../../prop_fs/SKIP_PRECOMPILE_HEADERS.rst:2
msgid "SKIP_PRECOMPILE_HEADERS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_fs/SKIP_PRECOMPILE_HEADERS.rst:6
msgid ""
"The file set sources will be skipped by :prop_tgt:`PRECOMPILE_HEADERS` "
"feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_fs/SKIP_PRECOMPILE_HEADERS.rst:8
msgid ""
"This property helps with build problems that one would run into when using "
"the :prop_tgt:`PRECOMPILE_HEADERS` feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../prop_fs/SKIP_PRECOMPILE_HEADERS.rst:11
msgid ""
"One example would be the usage of Objective-C (``*.m``) files, and Objective-"
"C++ (``*.mm``) files, which lead to compilation failure because they are "
"treated (in case of Ninja / Makefile generator) as C, and CXX respectively. "
"The precompile headers are not compatible between languages."
msgstr ""

